description:
KFF is the independent source of health policy research, polling, and news. Our mission is to fill the need for trusted information on national health issues all with a focus on how health policy affects people. KFF is a nonprofit and nonpartisan organization.

Position Summary:

KFF’s Human Resources Team works collaboratively to provide a wide range of HR services and support to our staff. We are seeking an energetic and detail oriented Human Resources Coordinator to provide critical support to our general HR functions across the team, playing a key role in supporting KFF’s recruiting efforts, coordinating responses to internal inquiries, administering leaves of absence, and various other tasks and projects. The ideal candidate will be service-oriented with strong communication and interpersonal skills, highly organized and resourceful with excellent follow-through, and capable of providing the highest level of support and assistance to internal staff and to external job candidates. This position will be privy to highly confidential information and will be responsible for maintaining strict confidentiality of such information at all times . This is a full-time position reporting to the Associate Director, Staffing and Employee Engagement, based in KFF’s Washington, DC office. The Coordinator will also work closely with KFF’s San Francisco-based HR staff on a regular basis.
Principal Duties and Responsibilities:

General HR Functions
The HR Coordinator will provide day-to-day support across the team on various HR related projects and tasks, including but not limited to the following:
Responsible for triaging and tracking internal and external inquiries submitted to the HR email box, working with HR colleagues to ensure a timely response and resolution to all inquiries;
Coordinate and monitor employee leaves of absence, serving as the point of contact for staff on leave, ensuring all paperwork is complete and submitted, while collaborating with Senior HR Managers and Payroll on all leave- related processes;
Assist in the management of worker’s compensation issues by assisting with required investigations of workplace related injuries and illnesses in KFF’s offices, and completing and submitting relevant paperwork for all worker’s compensation claims;
Responsible for maintaining and updating internal HR intranet pages with input and direction from HR colleagues;
Create and maintain an FAQ of commonly asked HR related questions to share with staff;
Assist with benefits enrollment for onboarding employees, enrollment terminations for offboarding employees, and during annual open enrollment periods;
Collaborate with other HR staff to maintain and update employee files and records including new hires, transfers, promotions, and terminations on an as needed basis;
Assist with verification of employment requests;
Keep apprised of various KFF sponsored webinars and events to flag for the HR team’s potential participation;
Run ad hoc reports as requested; and
Other HR related projects as assigned.

Recruiting
Support the Associate Director and HR Generalist in all aspects of the recruiting process, including, but not limited to the following:
Maintain KFF’s applicant tracking system, open position ad placements, and LinkedIn career page;
Participate in internal and external job fairs in support of KFF’s recruitment priorities;
Assist Hiring Managers with screening/interviewing candidates when needed;
Serve as primary backup for new hire I-9 and E-Verify processing;
Serve as a backup point of contact for job candidates during the application process; and
Assist with logistics associated with scheduling and planning interviews, meetings, presentations and trainings.

Minimum Desired Skills and Experience:

A passion for HR work is required. Must have either previous HR experience OR transferrable skills, with a minimum of 2-4 years of professional work experience;
Tact, discretion, and good self-expression with excellent interpersonal and communication skills, both written and verbal;
Ability to work independently and collaboratively, establish priorities, and self-manage multiple ongoing tasks and responsibilities with outstanding attention to detail;
Highly flexible and adaptable with excellent customer service skills;
Capacity to grasp new concepts and assignments quickly with highly developed organizational and time management skills;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office preferred. Experience working in BambooHR or other HRIS/ATS platforms desirable;
Skilled in building relationships and promptness in following up with both internal and external stakeholders; and
Authorization to work in the U.S.

This full-time position will be based in KFF’s Washington, DC office, located downtown near Metro Center. KFF is currently working a hybrid schedule and requires all staff to work in the office a minimum of two days a week.
Compensation
Salary is competitive and commensurate with experience and qualifications and includes an excellent benefits package.
The annual salary range for the Human Resource Coordinator position is between $75,000 and $90,000. Our job titles and salary ranges may span more than one career level, and the salary offered to a candidate will be determined based on factors such as the scope and responsibilities of the position, job related knowledge and skill set, depth of experience, certifications and/or degrees, and our practice of upholding salary equity within the organization.
How to Apply
If this position is of interest to you, and you have the requisite experience and qualifications, please apply.
KFF has an efficient applicant review process and will contact candidates who have applied for this position and whose qualifications most closely fit the criteria for the job. No phone inquiries please.
KFF requires all employees to be up-to-date on their COVID-19 vaccinations.
It is the policy of KFF to actively promote a diverse and inclusive workplace in every respect, and to provide equal employment opportunities to all qualified applicants and employees in every phase of employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, disability, veteran status, political affiliation, arrest or conviction records, or other categories protected under the law.

Summary
If you are a Dream-maker, this is the place for you. Together, we will create the real fabric of Gucci. A community of people united by the same passion: breaking new ground in the fashion world and beyond.
Job Description
Role Mission
The Gucci People Operations Coordinator is a departmental partner who works closely to support and coordinate the operational activities of the Human Resources team across all functional areas to ensure effective planning and implementation of Human Resources initiatives, policies, and procedures.
The People Operations Coordinator is responsible for assisting and supporting the West and Outlet markets, as well as being the primary contact to the workforce for designated functions.
Key Accountabilities
HR Administration and Operational Support
Assist with ongoing departmental needs and support the implementation of HR initiatives and projects;
Support the HRIS administration in Workday for recruitment, new hires, terminations, and changes in status;
Assist with coordination of worldwide special projects and worldwide visitors as needed;
Maintain department calendar and facilitate meetings;
Monitor, respond and forward inquiries from the Human Resources dedicated email inbox and hotline;
Maintain ad hoc recordkeeping, reporting and support as needed;
Consult with shared services to ensure procedural compliance;
Support with tracking and compliance with leave of absence and accommodation processes and recordkeeping;
Coordinate travel and accommodations as required for new hires and team members (training, corporate housing, relocation services etc.).
Recruiting and Onboarding
Support the recruitment process by creating offer letters and facilitating background checks;
Prepare employee letters as needed (i.e., Promotion, Title Change, Salary Change);
Oversee new hire preparations and set-up, inclusive of orientation, new hire paperwork collection, ID cards;
Maintain onboarding systems for accuracy in process flow and update documentation as necessary (i.e., HR Cloud, Monday.com).
Employee Relations
Function as a key resource for employees and managers on a variety of HR issues;
Support manager and employee inquiries regarding timekeeping, payroll inquiries and adjustments;
Prepare employment verification letters.
Training & Development
Support training initiatives as it pertains to managing scheduling of participants, ensure set-up of training facilities, procurement, and distribution of materials, training feedback and tracking, follow up reporting, etc.;
Manage training enrollments and progress in conjunction with legislative requirements (Harassment training, Code of Ethics, etc.).
Key Requirements
Bachelor's Degree (Human Resources concentration preferred) desired;
1-3 years of prior experience in Human Resources Functions;
Knowledge of Workday and Dayforce HRIS System (preferred);
Advanced Excel Skills;
Relevant experience gained within a fashion luxury retail environment;
Strong organization skills;
Ability to plan and manage multiple projects or tasks simultaneously;
Strong follow up skills on projects and activities on a day-to-day basis to maximize impact;
Demonstrated ability to develop and maintain effective work relationships with all levels of internal and external colleagues;
Strong interpersonal skills;
Ability to influence without authority and to work cross-functionally to deliver and share results;
Strong motivation to work for retail and the proven ability to work within a multi-site structure;
Can take responsibility for own actions;
Maintains objective view in negative or emotional situation.
Key Pillars for Ways of Working
Execute the mission of the role with a Radically Client-Centric mindset;
Approach activities and relationships with a methodology that promotes Flat, Connected and Fast ways of collaborative working;
Be Relentlessly Creative and approach challenges with an innovative mindset;
Demonstrate that Everyone is an Owner through thoughts, actions, and behaviors.
